dogecoin.text:
Whether you’re a bitcoin maximalist, bitcurious or a nocoiner, we’ve got you covered. Live Q&A this Friday.

Ask WSJ: From Bitcoin to Dogecoin: What's Happening With Crypto? https://t.co/Ca2h5L4u3l
What’re we even stressing about? Just give everybody an app and let ‘em trade dogecoin all day. Problem solved. https://t.co/kKprQdYMAJ
Flip on the radio this morning, scrolling through the channels, what’re they talking about on sports-talk radio? Dogecoin Musk SNL.

It's almost like people suddenly realized you shouldn't invest based on whether or not the host of a bad sketch comedy show mentions the asset you invested in. #dogecoin down 21%. https://t.co/InGhOZf9mC
Kinda looks like a middle finger, doesn't it? #dogecoin
"If the Chinese rocket lands on my head, at least I got to hear Elon Musk's mom say dogecoin on Saturday Night Live" is probably not something anybody is saying right now. DOGE down 23%.
And there you have it, crypto kids. Elon's mom said #dogecoin on national television. The thing is still down though. Guess it's a buy-the-rumor, sell-the-show selloff.

12 minutes in, and not even a reference to a dog, forget #dogecoin. This is a disaster for #crypto...

...and, there is it. From Elon's mom.

(Honestly, I can't believe this is financial journalism in 2021.)

#dogecoin falling, now down 8%, after Elon Musk isn't even brought on for the open of SNL.

(Seriously, I mean, this is what business reporters are actually, really doing in 2021. This is nuts.)
@WSJ On Saturday (Night Live), he called dogecoin a hustle. Today he stops taking bitcoin for Teslas. It's almost like Elon Musk doesn't take crypto as seriously as crypto people do.
